# ğŸ”¹ Pod Management

### List Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods
```
List all pods in the current namespace.

```bash
kubectl get pods --show-labels
```
List pods along with their labels.

```bash
kubectl get pod -o wide
```
Display additional details such as Node and Pod IP.

```bash
kubectl get pod --watch
```
Watch pods in real-time.

---

### Describe Pod

```bash
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
```
Display detailed information about a specific pod.

---

### Execute into Pod

```bash
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash
```
Access the container shell interactively.

```bash
exit
```
Exit from the container shell.

---

### View Pod Logs

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name>
```
View logs of a pod.

```bash
kubectl logs <pod-name> -c <container-name>
```
View logs of a specific container inside the pod.

---

### Delete Pod

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name>
```
Delete the specified pod.

---

### Create Pod Using Image

```bash
kubectl run <pod-name> --image=<image-name>
```
Create a pod using the specified container image.

