# ğŸ”¹ Deployment Management

### Create / Apply Deployment

```bash
kubectl create -f <manifest-file>.yml
```
Create resources from a YAML file.

```bash
kubectl apply -f <manifest-file>.yml
```
Create or update resources declaratively.

---

### View Deployments

```bash
kubectl get deploy
```
List all deployments.

```bash
kubectl get deploy -o wide
```
Show detailed deployment information.

```bash
kubectl get deploy --watch
```
Watch deployments in real-time.

---

### Describe Deployment

```bash
kubectl describe deploy <deployment-name>
```
Display detailed information about a deployment.

---

### Edit Deployment

```bash
kubectl edit deploy/<deployment-name>
```
Edit deployment configuration directly.

